755112: First of all, we need to load some packages for analyzing the data on the course. Or rather - we need these packages for manipulating, cleaning, and wrangling the data - and then conduct our analysis. When working with quantitative data, most time is actually spent manipulating data - and therefore we need some packages to do so. On this course we will mainly work with the tidyverse, an opinionatedcollection of R packagesdesigned for data science. All packages share an underlying design philosophy, grammar, and data structures.
Please load all the packages in section 0.1.

The political issue environment, is undergoing a positive development during the election campaign from the 10th-31st October. 

Assuming that the responses have been coded so "no" = 0 and "yes" = 1, we see that the start value is around 0.13 on the 10th October and it is rising slowly to around 0.15 on the 30th October.

Around the 23rd October, there is a development of a increase in people who selected "Environment" as the most important issue.

column23:
'agendaHealth' measure how many respondents find that the Health-topic is the most important topic/agenda in the election.

'agendaEnvironment' measure how many respondents find that the environmental agenda is the most important topic/agenda in the election.

'agendaImmigration' measure how many respondents find that the Immigration-topic is the most important topic/agenda in the election.

'agendaEconomy' measure how many respondents find that the Economy is the most important topic/agenda in the election.

 

The political issue of immigration is relatively stable in regards to how many respondents that find it important, but after the 24th of October the data shows a slight increase in how many, who find it important.

* AgendaHealth = for 3213 respondents, Health is the most important political issue 

* AgendaEnvironment = for 1452 respondents, Environment is the most important political issue

* AgendaImmigration = for 518 respondents, immigration is the most important political issue 

* AgendaEconomy = for 1679 respondents, Economy is the most important political issue 

The development of Health

The health agenda became increasingly important for the respondents throughout the election campaign, peaking on the 27/10 and then decreasing a bit until the last day 31/10

column23:
Through out the election periode the average share of the respondents/voters who has immigration as their number one priority for the politicians to address is 4,7%.
In the beginning of the election campaign the share of voters has Immigration as their key issue is above the average.

As the political campaign progress, the share of voters who has immigration as their key issue slowly decline. This decline in the share happens between the 5th of October until the 24th of October where there is a change in the 'trend'. From the 24th of October and to the end of the election campaigns (31st of October), there is an incline in the share of voters who has immigration as their key issue. 

Said in a more simple way: 
It seems like the voters slowly loose interest in the issue of immigration from the start of the election campaigns, but that they regain their interest in the issue in the last week of the election as they are getting closer to making their decision and vote.

During the period in which the data is collected, the political issue econonomy is the most important issue in the election for around 14-16% of the voters.

 

It is at its highest in the period from the 5th to the 16th October as it takes up a 16.5% share of the agenda. It then drops to the lowest level at around 14% on the 22th of October, but raises to around 16% in the end of the data collection (31th of October).
